  - run git container
  - pull workspace git repo
  - pull latest workspace images from registry
  - docker compose up into workspace git repo
  - ssh connect into the workspace jump
  - infinite loop: exit to kill the term after the loop (+ add a trap to exit)
- new host/init.sh:
  - load prompt.sh into .bashrc
- new workspace dir (1 workspace = 1 Dockerfile):
  - new Dockerfiles:
    - jump:
      - use ssh between containers
      - TMUX is installed here
    - workspace draft: manual installation & testing here
    - workspace admin (dind): workspaces git repo is managed here
    - workspace repo: aliases/packages for a managed git repository
    - workspace pro: aliases/packages for pro usage
    - gui: firefox, text editors, ...
- update workspace Dockerfiles + images with bot
  - templating for Dockerfiles

